    "final_answer": "In 2025, enterprise companies are adopting various AI technologies and applications, including Generative AI, Agentic AI, and Specialized Language Models, to manage complex operations and improve decision-making [Q1]. These technologies are being used to drive autonomous systems, multimodal AI, and intelligent automation, enabling companies to compete on customer experience through hyper-personalization [Q1]. Additionally, companies are leveraging AI for enterprise search and autonomous agents to execute multi-step workflows [Q1].\n\nTo mitigate risks, enterprise companies are implementing strategies to manage and mitigate supply chain risks, such as diversifying suppliers, nearshoring, and using digital twins to simulate disruptions [Q2]. They are also assessing supplier risks and building resilient supply chains to ensure business continuity [Q2].\n\nIn terms of remote work, companies are adopting flexible policies and practices, including flexible hours, asynchronous collaboration, and employee well-being initiatives [Q3]. They are also formalizing hybrid policies, requiring employees to be in the office a few days a week, and investing in tools and processes for distributed work, such as asynchronous video communication and digital whiteboarding [Q3]. By implementing these policies and technologies, enterprise companies are adapting to the changing business landscape and positioning themselves for success in 2025.",
